header: Test vectors of type JwCrypto are intended for tests that verify the
operations of a JSON Web Encryption/Signature library.

notes.JsonSerialization: The JWE/JWS is encoded with JSON serialization instead of compact serialization.
notes.WrongCipher: A key was used with the wrong cryptographic primitive.
notes.Pkcs15WithOaepKey: The private key is an RSA-OAEP key, but the encryption uses PKCS #1.5 padding
notes.ModifiedPkcs15Padding: The PKCS #1 padding has been modified. Padding errors should not be distinguishable.
